	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The info already exists in a doccument by drk414 available on the NesDev main page. (it explain how to change TKROM to TNROM)
<br />Change TSROM to TNROM should be possible, but a lot trickier due to the lack of on-board battery. I guess you should apply the same as TKROM to TNROM, and after that you should either replace the SRAM chip by a Dallas self-battery-backed SRAM, which would save a lot of trouble, but they are expensive and they will probably never fit a NES cart or even a frontloader NES console because the chips looks high. Alternatively, you can find a way to add the 2 diodes, 2 resistors and the battery needed for the backup circuit without a board for them by wiring them on the go and find a way to make it fit the cartridge.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


